          "date": "2018-02-01 19:20:34.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-10570 obd: use ktime_t for statfs handling",
        "message": "LU-10570 obd: use ktime_t for statfs handling\n\nThe comment 'use the value of cfs_time_current + HZ' for\nobd_statfs() and obd_statfs_async() gave the impression\nthat stats were refreshed when more than one second passed\nthus making it safe to use time64_t. This is not true and\nwe need to use finer time resolution. Migrate to ktime_t\ninstead. Remove the outdated comment as well.\n\nChange-Id: I0fe9ca5156706608a1ae40163b501b7334c5667a\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
